## 📊 Attack Types vs SIDs

### Boolean-Based SQLi
```
Payload: admin' OR 1=1 --
SID: 1000200 (OR 1=1)
SID: 1000201 (AND boolean)
SID: 1000202 (String comparison)
```

### UNION-Based SQLi
```
Payload: ' UNION SELECT * FROM users --
SID: 1000207 (SELECT FROM)
SID: 1000208 (UNION SELECT)
SID: 1000209 (UNION NULL enum)
```

### Time-Based Blind SQLi
```
Payload: ' AND SLEEP(5) --
SID: 1000210 (SLEEP)
SID: 1000211 (BENCHMARK)
SID: 1000212 (WAITFOR)
SID: 1000213 (DBMS_LOCK)
```

### Error-Based SQLi
```
Payload: ' AND EXTRACTVALUE(...) --
SID: 1000214 (EXTRACTVALUE)
SID: 1000215 (UPDATEXML)
SID: 1000216 (GTID_SUBSET)
```

### Stacked Queries
```
Payload: '; DROP TABLE users --
SID: 1000217 (DROP/TRUNCATE)
SID: 1000218 (DELETE)
SID: 1000219 (INSERT/UPDATE)
```

### File I/O
```
Payload: ' INTO OUTFILE '/path' --
SID: 1000220 (INTO OUTFILE)
SID: 1000221 (INTO DUMPFILE)
SID: 1000222 (LOAD DATA INFILE)
```

### RCE (MSSQL/PostgreSQL)
```
Payload: '; xp_cmdshell 'cmd' --
SID: 1000223 (xp_cmdshell)
SID: 1000224 (sp_oacreate)
SID: 1000225 (sp_executesql)
SID: 1000226 (sys_exec)
```

### Data Extraction
```
Payload: ' GROUP_CONCAT(...) --
SID: 1000227 (GROUP_CONCAT)
SID: 1000228 (CAST)
SID: 1000229 (INFORMATION_SCHEMA)
SID: 1000230 (mysql.user)
```

### Encoding/Bypass
```
Payload: %00 or /* */ comment
SID: 1000231 (NULL byte)
SID: 1000232 (Multiline comment)
```

